The ketone functional group also increases the melting point through dipole-dipole interactions; however, since we already accounted for substantial polarity increases, its effect will be moderate, estimated at +10 degrees. Prediction: Starting with the base value of the melting point for benzene at 5.5°C, we can add the estimated increments: +40 (phenyl) + 70 (amide) + 60 (two trifluoromethyl groups) + 20 (pyrazole) + 10 (ketone) = 5.5 + 40 + 70 + 60 + 20 + 10 = 205.5°C.
